const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Are these GEO tool reviews sponsored or affiliated?',
    a: 'No. All reviews on GEOoptimised are written independently. We do not accept payment for reviews, do not use affiliate links, and do not allow vendors to influence editorial content. Our assessments are based on direct evaluation and publicly available information. Where we have a commercial relationship with a vendor for any other purpose, we disclose it explicitly.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do you evaluate GEO tools?',
    a: 'We assess tools against six criteria: platform coverage (which AI platforms are monitored), citation tracking granularity (URL-level versus brand-level), entity analysis capability, pricing model and value, ease of use for practitioners, and data collection methodology. Each review explains how the tool performs against each criterion and what types of GEO programme it is best suited to.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the difference between a GEO tool and an SEO tool?',
    a: 'Traditional SEO tools measure rankings, backlinks, and organic traffic in search engines like Google. GEO tools measure brand citation frequency, entity presence, and AI answer visibility across generative platforms like ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini. The two categories are complementary: SEO tools track performance in traditional search; GEO tools track performance in AI-generated answers.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do tools like Semrush and Ahrefs support GEO workflows?',
    a: 'Partially. Semrush and Ahrefs have both added AI visibility features, but their core infrastructure is built for traditional search. Their GEO-adjacent features are useful supplements to a dedicated GEO tool, not replacements for one. Our reviews of Semrush for GEO and Ahrefs for GEO cover which specific features are genuinely useful and which are primarily marketing.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Are there free GEO tools worth using?',
